org.nasdanika.codegen.ecore.web.ui.model

Interface ENamedElementConfiguration

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CDOObject, CDOWithID, EModelElementConfiguration, EObject, Notifier
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    EAttributeConfiguration, EClassConfiguration, EReferenceConfiguration, EStructuralFeatureConfiguration, ETypedElementConfiguration
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EAttributeConfigurationImpl, EClassConfigurationImpl, ENamedElementConfigurationImpl, EReferenceConfigurationImpl, EStructuralFeatureConfigurationImpl, ETypedElementConfigurationImpl

    public interface ENamedElementConfiguration
extends EModelElementConfiguration

    A representation of the model object ‘ENamed Element Configuration’.

    The following features are supported:

    • Model Element Label
    • Constraints
    • Sort
    See Also:
    ModelPackage.getENamedElementConfiguration()

      • getConstraints

        String getConstraints()

        Returns the value of the ‘Constraints’ attribute. Constraint shall be a YML text which defines a single constraint or a list of constraints. Constraint can be a string or a map containing:

        • condition - XPath expression boolean expression.
        • errorMessageKey - Optional error message key. If it is present, error message is retrieved as resource string.
        • errorMessage - Error message to display if the expression evaluates to false. It is used if errorMessageKey is not defined or if there is no resource string for the key.

        If the constraint is a String, then it is treated as condition XPath expression and error message is constructed as Constraint violation: <condition>.

        Returns:
        the value of the ‘Constraints’ attribute.
        See Also:
        setConstraints(String), ModelPackage.getENamedElementConfiguration_Constraints()
